<item>
            <title>[JDK-8299079] Better interface nmethod oop accesses</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8299079</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Today when oops are read from nmethods, we use the same interfacing that we would use to read any other IN_NATIVE oops. That isn&amp;#39;t enough for generational ZGC. The nmethod oops are rather different from other IN_NATIVE oops in that they are encoded in the machine code as direct pointers. Normally, IN_NATIVE oops with generational ZGC are not direct pointers, but are colored pointered that can be converted to direct pointers by going through a load barrier. For nmethod oops, that conversion requires external knowledge from the surrounding nmethod. I propose a new NMethodAccess to interface better with the GC.</description>
